Scenario: An adopter who follows the documentation end-to-end arrives at a lead-shop container plus per-BC containers running and can dispatch their first scenario
  Given the shopsystem-docs repository contains an adoption walkthrough (one or more linked markdown files) starting from the entry document
  And an adopter has executed every step the walkthrough names, in order, on a host with Docker installed
  When the adopter completes the final step the walkthrough specifies
  Then the adopter's host has a lead-shop container running for their own product
  And the adopter's host has one container running per BC the adopter's manifest declares
  And every running BC container is registered with the messaging registry such that "shop-msg registry list" shows the BC name and its container-side path
  And the adopter can open a Claude Code session against the lead-shop container and dispatch an assign_scenarios message to one of their BCs without performing any step the walkthrough did not name
